al historical junctures—on the eve of the creation of the Jewish state, he played a key role articulating Israel's relationship with diaspora Jewry, postwar Germany, and the Arab world. This volume captures Goldmann in all his complexity, while making this important figure and his time accessible to researchers, students, and interested readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aZionistsvBiography. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh1 aBrenner, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChazan, Meir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriesel, Evyatar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorny, Yosef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorat, Dina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaider, Mark A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaider, Mark A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReinharz, Jehuda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRutland, Suzanne D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegev, Zohar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShafir, Shlomo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShimoni, Gideon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZweig, Ronald W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438425153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.c